com.b2international.snowowl.snomed.snomedrefset

Interface SnomedComplexMapRefSetMember

  • All Superinterfaces:
    org.eclipse.emf.cdo.CDOObject, org.eclipse.emf.cdo.common.id.CDOWithID, org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject, org.eclipse.emf.common.notify.Notifier, SnomedRefSetMember, SnomedSimpleMapRefSetMember
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    Rf2RefSetMember, SnomedComplexMapRefSetMemberImpl, UnsupportedRf2RefSetMember

    public interface SnomedComplexMapRefSetMember
extends SnomedSimpleMapRefSetMember
    Represents a complex map type reference set member. Its purpose is to establish mapping between a given SNOMED CT concept and one or more codes in a target scheme.

    The following features are supported:

    • Map Group
    • Map Priority
    • Map Rule
    • Map Advice
    • Correlation Id

    See Also:
    SnomedRefSetPackage.getSnomedComplexMapRefSetMember()

      • getMapCategoryId

        String getMapCategoryId()
        Returns with a SNOMED CT concept ID representing the map category for the current complex map type reference set. The followings can be interpreted as the map category:
        • Properly classified.
        • Patient context employed in map rule property for the mapping.
        • Cannot be classified with available data.
        Returns:
        the concept ID of the map category for the complex map type reference set member.
        See Also:
        setMapCategoryId(String), SnomedRefSetPackage.getSnomedComplexMapRefSetMember_MapCategoryId()
